defined_class_definition: Surgical removal of an abnormal pouch of the lining of the small intestine (bowel).

comment: Surgery to remove abnormal tissue or cancer from the breast and a small amount of normal tissue around it. It is a type of breast-sparing surgery. NCIT:C15755
syns: tylectomy|partial mastectomy| breast segmental resection|breast wide local|lumpectomy of breast excision

defined_class_definition: The surgical removal (cutting out) of part or all of colorectal polyps.
